### 1. Auto-Approve Software Expense
# Demonstrates: Successful Strategy routing and Type Guard validation
POST http://localhost:3000/approve/EXPENSE
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "amount": 450,
  "category": "Software",
  "currency": "GBP"
}

### 2. Manual Review - Business Rule Triggered
# Demonstrates: Logic inside the Software strategy (Threshold > 500)
POST http://localhost:3000/approve/EXPENSE
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "amount": 550,
  "category": "Software",
  "currency": "GBP"
}

### 3. Manual Review - Hardware Strategy
# Demonstrates: A domain-specific rule where all items require a human eye
POST http://localhost:3000/approve/EXPENSE
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "amount": 50,
  "category": "Hardware",
  "currency": "GBP"
}

### 4. Invalid Data Structure (Type Guard catch)
# Demonstrates: The Type Guard (isExpenseRequest) rejecting bad JSON before logic runs
POST http://localhost:3000/approve/EXPENSE
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "wrong_field": "This will fail validation",
  "amount": "not_a_number"
}

### 5. Unknown Domain (Registry/IoC catch)
# Demonstrates: The Hub's safety when a non-existent domain is requested
POST http://localhost:3000/approve/MARKETING
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "data": "irrelevant"
}